The paper discusses hardware cyber-security risks associated with channel decoders, which are commonly used in communication systems. This topic falls under the category of computer security and cryptography (cs.CR). Additionally, the paper proposes methods for mitigating these risks, which involve randomizing inputs and optimizing decoding performance. This suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the sub-categories of human-computer interaction (cs.HC), software engineering (cs.SE), information theory (cs.IT), and systems and control (cs.SY).
